   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <hazardstatement type="caution" class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
            <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
               <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard ">Unintended Equipment Operation</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">Only use original equipment manufacturer (OEM) BACS bus
cables. If the cables are substituted the overall function of the
battery monitoring system cannot be guaranteed.</howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <hazardstatement type="notice" class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
            <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
               <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard ">low signal strength</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">Do not use a BACS bus cable that is longer than the maximum
cable length specified for the connection.</howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <p class="- topic/p ">Before attaching the bus cables:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Consider the distances between the individual battery blocks
and choose the respective cable length accordingly. There are several
cable lengths to choose from.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">The module that is closest to the webmanager or the splitting
box should be the first one in the string. Keep one of the two bus
ports free and connect later with the splitting box or the webmanager.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Check the information and maximum distances for the bus cable
installation in the chapter <xref href="GBMS_Bus_Cable_Length_and_Wiring_Details_CPT_0000511676.dita"
                           scope="local"
                           type="concept"
                           class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">Attach the bus cables between all modules:</p>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Connect the bus cables between the modules in each row
of the battery bank. The maximum number of modules in a bus string
is 50.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/GBMS_Bus-cables_1_0000511665.png"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">If applicable, connect the bus cables between the modules
at the end of the rows.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/GBMS_Bus-cables_2_0000511664.png"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
               <note id="DoNotUseTheG.BMSModuleClosestToTheG-45D058B2" class="- topic/note ">Do not
use the module closest to the webmanager or splitting box to connect
the rows.</note>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">If applicable, connect the bus cables between the shelves
in the battery bank.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/GBMS_Bus-cables_3_0000511663.png"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Repeat applicable steps for each battery string.</cmd>
         </step>
      </steps>
